dataCsv.Site_Description: The Richard Winslow lies flattened in shallow water. It was dynamited as a shipping hazard but many features still remain. The site consists of the bottom of the ship which is covered with iron ore and the starboard side of the ship. There is scattered artifacts including wire rigging, a small boiler, and the hawse pipes. The side of the ship contains knees, pin rails, hawse pipes, wire rigging, bitts, and most of the bulwark. The keelson and at least one mast step is visible on the bottom piece.
